<p>- <strong>Humidifiers</strong>: Use a humidifier if your cellar is too dry, and a dehumidifier if it's too moist.</p>
<p><strong>Light Exposure</strong></p>
<p>- <strong>Minimal Light</strong>: Wines, particularly those in clear bottles, can be damaged by UV light.</p>
<p>- <strong>Storage Conditions</strong>: Store wines in a dark environment; if lighting is necessary, use LED lights as
  they emit minimal heat and UV rays.</p>
