<p>2. <strong>Cost Estimates</strong>: Obtain detailed cost estimates for both repair and replacement.</p>
<p>3. <strong>Consult Professionals</strong>: Seek expert advice and recommendations.</p>
<p>4. <strong>Weigh Pros and Cons</strong>: Evaluate the long-term benefits and potential drawbacks of both options.</p>
<p>5. <strong>Make an Informed Decision</strong>: Based on the assessment, cost analysis, and expert opinions, decide
